wanted design school student interested in freelance work arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe for students opportunities wanted design school student interested in freelance work deadline sunday april 1 2012 unpaid design brief our non profit company carbon lighthouse association buys carbon allowances from a carbon market to reduce a building's carbon footprint to zero it's the icing on the cake for our rad energy projects at the end of the project we present a wooden plaque to our client our first prototype plaque is attached it would be etched on wood however we think it could be improved vision we want the plaque to emphasize the 1 customer's environmental commitment to carbon free 2 the building's carbon free footprint 3 the project was done profitably ie this is financial & environmental responsibility at its best 4 carbon lighthouse role unit cost less than $100 for the finished product size license plate range benefit for student we re a start up so we don t really have the cash to hire somebody however it would be a real project for a real company and would definitely pave the way towards meeting the company's founders and principals work expectation 3 4 hours deadline 1 april 2012 interested contact matt ganser matt carbonlighthouse com contact matt carbonlighthouse com for more info listed in job off campus see all opportunities prospective students check out the arts guide your multimedia guide to the arts at stanford stay updated student home events calendar opportunities in review subscribe curricular info majoring minoring creativity course guide arts intensive arts immersion arts circle make it happen money supplies space collaboration promotion beyond stanford internships career resources bay area arts back to arts at stanford make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
